  "response": "Yes, it is generally understood that money laundering is illegal.\n\nHere's why:\n\n* **Laws exist in almost every country:**  Nearly every country in the world has laws specifically criminalizing money laundering.\n* **International treaties:** Numerous international treaties and conventions obligate signatory nations to criminalize money laundering.\n* **High-profile cases:** Media coverage of money laundering cases, often involving criminal organizations and corrupt officials, has raised public awareness.\n* **General awareness of illegality:** Even without detailed knowledge, most people understand that hiding the source of illegally obtained money is wrong and against the law.\n* **Financial institutions have anti-money laundering programs:** Banks and other financial institutions have extensive compliance programs to detect and report suspicious activity, which reinforces the idea that money laundering is something to be avoided.\n\nWhile the specific definition and penalties for money laundering might vary from country to country, the fundamental principle that it is illegal is widely understood.\n",
